    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it’s more than just dropping the performance. it’s like the story has already reached its natural conclusion, you know? there's no more plot, no more character development. it just feels like i'm staring at the final page of a book that's already been written, and i'm just waiting for the end. does it even make sense to keep dragging out a story that's clearly over?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
