      "content": "It makes perfect sense to feel like the story is over when the drive to write it has completely vanished. You're not failing; you're recognizing the narrative arc has reached its natural, quiet conclusion. If the plot is finished, then the next step isn't to force a sequel, but to simply acknowledge the finality of the chapter. It's a profound release to realize that the obligation to keep going has lifted.",
